A pet is what being a mage is all about. And pets should be the first and for most thing a mage thinks about. The fact that mages are happy over getting an improved fire pet is great. <br>
<br>
I'm also not going to pretend I understand all the woes of being a mage, but I can understand alot. Anyone saying someone else doesn't uderstand the problems with thier class doesn't see that every class has something about it they would like changed. Saying your problems are greater then other peoples problems comes across as immature. It doesn't support any arguement for or against this.<br>
<br>
Fire pets are better of with Draught of Fire then Ice Comet. Even at level 63. 2 DoF = 430 mana for 1286 (at level 51), which is a little more mana for alot more damage. And it casts VERY fast. And it makes sense for a fire elemental to cast this.<br>
<br>
Lures, no, for the simple fact that they are unresistable. That really does over power them. The mages I know don't just let thier pets do all the work. They heal and nuke along with thier pets. So besides the Damage from the pets DS, it's melee attacks, now there would be an unresitable 640 points of DD damage. Oh and what ever nukes the mages toss in themselves. <br>
<br>
I don't see any wizard claiming here that mages shouldn't be getting an upgrade. We just don't like how it's being done. And everytime we say this, Mages step around this fact. It's dishearting to say, We agree with you, you pet should be made better, only have mages come back and say we are simply trying to stop them. <br>
<br>
We've even said what spells we would have No Problem with your pet casting. And they are some dam fine spells. <br>
<br>
I have to say, I read through all 8 pages finally on your site, and was disheartened by the tone of it. Yes there are mages on both sides of it. As there are wizards on both sides of it.<br>
<br>
The name calling on both sides is childish at best. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>If we support mages getting better pets, then I would hope that mages would support wizards getting bigger nukes. But you don't. I can't see much support for this. Maybe if instead of trying to keep one or the other down, we simply try and make each other better?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
